text: Stara Kamienica () is a village in Jelenia Góra County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. It is the seat of the administrative district (gmina) called Gmina Stara Kamienica. It lies approximately west of Jelenia Góra, and west of the regional capital Wrocław. The village has a population of 1,200. ==References== Stara Kamienica
